<p>

After spending time working in technology on Wall Street, Sacks has since 2004 worked as Head of Global Applications Development the online bond trading company, MarketAxess. He was also employed by Morgan Stanley from 1994 to 2004, as Director, Global Head of Bond Technology for the Fixed Income Division. At Morgan Stanley he was Chief Operating Officer for Fixed Income Technology and Global Head of Technology for the Foreign Exchange Division. Prior to Morgan Stanley he held positions at Salomon Brothers, Inc. and IBM Research Division. Mr. Sacks has an A.B. in Social Relations from Harvard College and a M.S. in Computer Science from Columbia University.</p>

